reactor.bus.filter

Interface Filter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FirstFilter, PassThroughFilter, RandomFilter, RoundRobinFilter, TraceableDelegatingFilter

    public interface Filter
    A Filter is used to filter a list of items. The nature of the filtering is determined by the implementation.
    Author:
    Andy Wilkinson

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <T> List<T> filter(List<T> items, Object key)
      Filters the given List of items.

    • Method Detail

      • filter

        <T> List<T> filter(List<T> items,
                   Object key)
        Filters the given List of items. The key may be used by an implementation to influence the filtering.
        Parameters:
        items - The items to filter. Must not be null.
        key - The key
        Returns:
        The filtered items, never null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if items is null
